# Development Workflow Standards

## 🛠️ Primary Development Focus

### Core Development Areas
1. **[scripts/unified_app.py](mdc:scripts/unified_app.py)** - Main Streamlit interface (PRIMARY WORK LOCATION)
2. **Module Integration** - Backend connectivity and optimization
3. **Theme Refinement** - Dark Mode Pro styling improvements
4. **Platform Optimization** - Per-platform feature tuning
5. **Documentation Maintenance** - Keep unified approach current

### Primary Work Location
**Most development happens in:** `scripts/unified_app.py`
- Main Streamlit application (600+ lines)
- Page-based navigation system
- All UI components and user interactions
- Integration point for all backend modules

### Development Priorities
- **Simplicity:** Maintain single-cell approach
- **Performance:** Optimize for speed and efficiency  
- **User Experience:** Professional interface with real-time feedback
- **Compatibility:** Support maximum platform/extension compatibility
- **Documentation:** Keep comprehensive, organized documentation current

## 🧪 Testing Requirements

### Unified Architecture Testing
```bash
# Primary testing commands
streamlit run scripts/unified_app.py --server.port 8501
jupyter notebook notebook/SD-DarkMaster-Pro-Unified.ipynb
python Utilities/comprehensive_testing_tool.py
```

### Critical Testing Rules
- **ALWAYS** test unified single-cell approach
- **NEVER** test obsolete multi-cell architecture  
- **VERIFY** Streamlit interface functionality
- **TEST** all page navigation and state persistence
- **VALIDATE** tunnel creation and public access
- **CONFIRM** platform detection and optimization

### Performance Validation
- **Deployment Speed:** ≤ 30 seconds target
- **Storage Efficiency:** ≥ 68% space savings verification
- **Extension Compatibility:** Test 29/31 working extensions
- **Platform Support:** Verify 12+ platform compatibility
- **UI Responsiveness:** Real-time updates working

## 📝 Code Quality Standards

### Python Code Requirements
- **Type Hints:** Use type annotations for all functions
- **Error Handling:** Comprehensive exception handling with user-friendly messages
- **Logging:** Structured logging with appropriate levels
- **Documentation:** Docstrings for all classes and functions
- **Performance:** Async operations where applicable (downloads, I/O)

### Streamlit Standards
- **State Management:** All persistent data in `st.session_state`
- **Page Structure:** Consistent navigation and layout
- **Real-time Updates:** Progress tracking and status displays
- **Theme Compliance:** Dark Mode Pro styling throughout
- **Error Display:** User-friendly error messages and recovery options

### Module Integration
- **Core Modules:** Platform detection, theme engine, storage management
- **Enterprise Modules:** Advanced features like unified storage and download management
- **Clean Interfaces:** Well-defined APIs between modules
- **Configuration:** Centralized configuration management
- **Extensibility:** Modular design for easy feature addition

## 🔄 Development Workflow

### Feature Development Process
1. **Plan in Documentation** - Update relevant docs first
2. **Implement in Modules** - Core functionality in backend modules
3. **Integrate in UI** - Add to appropriate Streamlit page
4. **Test Thoroughly** - All testing requirements met
5. **Update Documentation** - Reflect changes in numbered docs
6. **Update AI Status** - Trigger AI-maintained document updates

### Code Review Checklist
- [ ] Maintains single-cell architecture principles
- [ ] Integrates properly with Streamlit interface
- [ ] Follows unified storage and module patterns
- [ ] Includes comprehensive error handling
- [ ] Updates relevant documentation
- [ ] Passes all testing requirements
- [ ] Maintains performance standards

## 🎯 Integration Standards

### Streamlit Page Integration
New features MUST integrate with existing page structure:
```python
# Required integration pattern
def new_feature_page():
    st.title("🔧 New Feature")
    
    # State management
    if 'feature_state' not in st.session_state:
        st.session_state.feature_state = {}
    
    # Feature implementation
    # ...
    
    # Progress tracking
    # Real-time status updates
```

### Module Development
- **Core Modules:** Essential functionality in `modules/core/`
- **Enterprise Modules:** Advanced features in `modules/enterprise/`
- **Clean APIs:** Well-defined interfaces and error handling
- **Configuration Integration:** Use centralized config system
- **Performance Optimization:** Async operations and caching

### Storage Integration
All new features MUST use:
- **[modules/enterprise/unified_storage_manager.py](mdc:modules/enterprise/unified_storage_manager.py)** for file operations
- Symbolic link management for space efficiency
- Cross-WebUI compatibility (A1111/ComfyUI/Forge)
- Metadata tracking and integrity verification

